lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Bernie Sanders, whose $18 million fund-raising haul has solidified his status as a front-runner for the Democratic presidential nomination, said Tuesday that he would release 10 years of tax returns by Tax Day on Monday and acknowledged that he has joined the ranks of the millionaires he has denounced for years.

abstract: In the On Politics newsletter, Kirstjen Nielsen’s dismissal was the latest in President Trump’s convention breaking with the so-called “norms” that long governed the capital.

abstract: After 24 years in charge of the left-leaning weekly’s editorial operations, the second woman to serve as its editor will give up running that role while continuing on as publisher.
snippet: After 24 years in charge of the left-leaning weekly’s editorial operations, the second woman to serve as its editor will give up running that role while continuing on as publisher.
lead_paragraph: For 24 years, the editor and publisher Katrina vanden Heuvel has been the public face of The Nation, the oldest continuously published weekly in the United States. On June 15, she will give up her job as day-to-day editor, and be succeeded in the role by D. D. Guttenplan, an author long associated with the magazine.

abstract: The senator’s fund-raising total includes an undisclosed amount that she could spend only in a general election campaign, not in the primary.
snippet: The senator’s fund-raising total includes an undisclosed amount that she could spend only in a general election campaign, not in the primary.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Amy Klobuchar of Minnesota raised more than $5.2 million over the first seven weeks of her presidential bid, her campaign said on Monday, though that sum includes an undisclosed amount she could spend only in a general election campaign, not in the Democratic primary.

lead_paragraph: Senator Cory Booker of New Jersey announced on Sunday that his presidential campaign had raised more than $5 million in the first quarter of the year.
